content:
I'm wondering if there is any significance to the * that appears next to a lot of the entries on this table.
http://hl7-fhir.github.io/w5.html
There is no explanation for it. Does it just mean "partially classifies"?
I think it means 0..* as opposed to 0..1

Meta: if there's a channel more appropriate to w5 governance, let me know
I wrote a little script to summarize where we are on w5 mappings. https://github.com/ericprud/fhir-w5/blob/main/README.md.
I'm interested in feedback on my categories.
I would agree that FiveWs is not as well promoted as it should be. I suspect this is simply a fact of priortization, where more critical modeling methodology items have taken priority.

i'm back from vacation and will be working on this this week. happy to geek with anyone
(looking at you, @John Moehrke )
